==Translingual==
===Etymology===
From [[w:Charles Messier|Charles Messier]], who first published ''Nebulae and Star Clusters'' in 1774 as a listing of visible objects in the night sky that were not stars. Objects in Messier's catalog are numbered, and the letter '''M''' (for Messier) is prepended to these numbers.
==={{abbreviation}}===
{{wikipedia}}
'''M31'''

#{{astronomy}}: The [[Andromeda]] [[galaxy|Galaxy]]; a giant [[spiral]] galaxy in the [[Local Group]], together with the [[Milky Way]] galaxy. It is at a distance of approximately 2.5 million [[light year]]s from Earth, in the direction of the [[constellation]] Andromeda.

